{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/21st-century-cave-paintings/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"1Percent Blog  Kiran Anto"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"2ad078d7-15d0-5ebc-bf0f-e5053a8a0fe0","excerpt":"Today is more of an exploration of iconography. Iconography is my latest new hobby, ğŸ“˜ learning more on iconography, ğŸ” identifying the ğŸ’­ thought processâ€¦","html":"<p>Today is more of an exploration of iconography. Iconography is my latest new hobby, ğŸ“˜ learning more on iconography, ğŸ” identifying the ğŸ’­ thought process behind the creation of icons, what to consider while creating icons, how to ensure their consistency etc.</p>\n<p>My Colleague, Dinesha Kumar was more than happy to take an hour of class on iconography and pictorials and set the direction ğŸ¯. Itâ€™s an honour to have a great mentor who could shed light in these areas throughout the journey.</p>\n<p>Icons are lifesavers in this world of noise and worthless information. You only need a quick look at an icon to get the complex message it carries. Icons unite the entire world ğŸŒ. It doesnâ€™t matter what language you speak â€“ the one visual language of icons speaks louder ğŸ“¢ than any words can.</p>\n<p>There are different types of icons based on their styles</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Outline icons</li>\n<li>Filled icons</li>\n<li>Glyph icons</li>\n<li>Flat icons</li>\n<li>Hand drawn icons</li>\n<li>Skewmorphic icons</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Outline icons are one of my favourites ğŸ’–, I admire what Microsoft does with their iconography. These are well thought out, clean iconography.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Creating one beautiful icon is easy. Creating a few good looking icons isnâ€™t that hard either. Itâ€™s making them cohesive that can knock you down.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6c7cb3c645a3e545c35ae4a7e36fdbb2/21b4d/microsoft.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.08108108108109%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Microsoft outline icons\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/6c7cb3c645a3e545c35ae4a7e36fdbb2/fcda8/microsoft.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6c7cb3c645a3e545c35ae4a7e36fdbb2/12f09/microsoft.png 148w,\n/static/6c7cb3c645a3e545c35ae4a7e36fdbb2/e4a3f/microsoft.png 295w,\n/static/6c7cb3c645a3e545c35ae4a7e36fdbb2/fcda8/microsoft.png 590w,\n/static/6c7cb3c645a3e545c35ae4a7e36fdbb2/efc66/microsoft.png 885w,\n/static/6c7cb3c645a3e545c35ae4a7e36fdbb2/c83ae/microsoft.png 1180w,\n/static/6c7cb3c645a3e545c35ae4a7e36fdbb2/21b4d/microsoft.png 1280w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>I was thinking that the outline icons and filled icons are just a matter of user preference and adds to aesthetics only but looks like thereâ€™s much more than that. Itâ€™s picked based on the speed at which you can grasp the characteristic cues in the icon. The image below showâ€™s it better.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 420px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ad85fbaa9bb9fdfc9c9080334030994b/d10fb/outline_icons.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 101.35135135135135%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Outline icons faster characteristic cues\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/ad85fbaa9bb9fdfc9c9080334030994b/d10fb/outline_icons.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ad85fbaa9bb9fdfc9c9080334030994b/12f09/outline_icons.png 148w,\n/static/ad85fbaa9bb9fdfc9c9080334030994b/e4a3f/outline_icons.png 295w,\n/static/ad85fbaa9bb9fdfc9c9080334030994b/d10fb/outline_icons.png 420w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>More on that.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 534px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6f002512e40e2eaafe177fa0300d558f/a07a7/outline_icons_2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 57.432432432432435%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Outline icons faster characteristic cues\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/6f002512e40e2eaafe177fa0300d558f/a07a7/outline_icons_2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6f002512e40e2eaafe177fa0300d558f/12f09/outline_icons_2.png 148w,\n/static/6f002512e40e2eaafe177fa0300d558f/e4a3f/outline_icons_2.png 295w,\n/static/6f002512e40e2eaafe177fa0300d558f/a07a7/outline_icons_2.png 534w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 534px) 100vw, 534px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>There are scenarios when solid icons are faster, that is when the icons represent physical objects in the real world. Viewing them in solid icons would give a much more realastic approach.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 390px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7cf2ac9edd4c7f0aa6e8b8f50756a46e/727ba/filled_icons.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 115.54054054054055%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Sometimes filled icons are faster\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/7cf2ac9edd4c7f0aa6e8b8f50756a46e/727ba/filled_icons.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7cf2ac9edd4c7f0aa6e8b8f50756a46e/12f09/filled_icons.png 148w,\n/static/7cf2ac9edd4c7f0aa6e8b8f50756a46e/e4a3f/filled_icons.png 295w,\n/static/7cf2ac9edd4c7f0aa6e8b8f50756a46e/727ba/filled_icons.png 390w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 390px) 100vw, 390px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>So choosing whether to go with outline icons or filled icons can only be done based on the concept of the app and what suits better. When choosing icons, itâ€™s best to stick to a consistent style. Instead of mixing solid and outline styles, try to choose a set of icons that have salient characteristic cues with sharper angles that point outward.</p>\n<p>For more info visit - <a href=\"https://uxmovement.com/mobile/solid-vs-outline-icons-which-are-faster-to-recognize/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">UXMovement | Solid Vs. Outline Icons: Which Are Faster to Recognize?</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"so-coming-back-to-icons-how-can-we-make-it-better\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#so-coming-back-to-icons-how-can-we-make-it-better\" aria-label=\"so coming back to icons how can we make it better permalink\" class=\"header-links before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>So coming back to icons. How can we make it better?</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Keep The Same Stylistics</li>\n<li>Size Matters! - Stick to same size</li>\n<li>Try Using Grids</li>\n<li>Use The Same Color Palette</li>\n</ol>\n<p><em>This is where iâ€™ve reached so far. Will keep posted on my readings on iconography.</em></p>\n<p>If youâ€™re starting a new project and donâ€™t want to go through all these troubles of creating consistent, clean icons, we have a solution in front us, Donâ€™t re-invent the wheel unless necessary. There are lots of icon providers</p>\n<ol>\n<li>IconFinder - 4,438,576 icons</li>\n<li>NounProject - Over 2 Million curated icons</li>\n<li>Flat icon - 2,876,500 Icons</li>\n<li>Icon8 - 129,200 FREE ICONS</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Adios for the day ğŸ‘‹</p>","timeToRead":2,"frontmatter":{"title":"Icons - 21st Century Cave paintings ğŸ”£","date":"May 24, 2020","description":"Learning more on iconography, identifying the thought process behind the creation of icons, what to consider while creating icons, how to ensure their consistency etc. "}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/21st-century-cave-paintings/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/new-beginnings/"},"timeToRead":1,"frontmatter":{"title":"New Beginnings ğŸ”°"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/gatsby-improves-performance/"},"timeToRead":3,"frontmatter":{"title":"How Gatsby drastically improves web development ğŸ“ˆ"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383","3182425314"],"slicesMap":{}}